
# Local environment variables used when running Maestro E2E tests.
# This file is gitignored.
#
# Copy this file to:
#
#   .env.local
#
# and adjust values for your machine.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# How this file is used
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Maestro itself does NOT read `.env` files.
#
# Instead, environment variables must be passed to Maestro
# explicitly using:
#
#   -e KEY=value
#
# Example:
#
#   maestro test tests/landing.yml -e EXPO_APP_DEEPLINK=...
#
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Two ways to consume this file
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
#  1. Recommended: via the wrapper script
#
#   apps/betterangels/.maestro/scripts/maestro-e2e.sh
#
# This script:
#   • reads `.env.local`
#   • converts each line into `-e KEY=value`
#   • runs the Maestro CLI with those variables
#
# Example:
#
#   -p ios
#   --platform ios
#   --verbose
#   --verbose -p ios (--verbose come first)

#   yarn e2e:dev -p ios (or android) (runs all tests)
#   yarn e2e:dev -p ios <yml filename> (`landing.yml` or just `landing`)
#   yarn e2e:dev --verbose -p ios
#   yarn e2e:dev --verbose -p ios landing
#
#
# 2. Manual CLI usage (requires parsing)
#
# If running Maestro directly, this file must be converted into
# `-e KEY=value` arguments first.
#
# Example:
#
#   maestro test tests \
#     $(grep -v '^#' .env.local | sed 's/^/-e /')
#
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required variables
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Deep link used to open the Expo development client.
#
# This should point to the running Expo dev server on your machine.
# Replace the IP address with your local network address if needed.
#
# You can find this value in the Expo CLI output when running:
#
#   yarn nx run betterangels:start
#

EXPO_APP_DEEPLINK=exp+betterangels://expo-development-client/?url=http://192.168.1.198:8081
